{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DgwUhVA7B2ZHFmHw1wNGAb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me provide a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully identified the \"project page workflow view\" issue where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load file contents. The problem is in the **API handler** that serves step content.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe bug is in the **`handleAPIStepContent` function** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199).\n\n**The Issue:** When a prompt file cannot be read (line 1177-1182), the handler falls through to the next condition instead of returning an error. This happens when:\n1. A step has a `prompt` config pointing to a file (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/fix.md`)\n2. The file exists and the path is correct\n3. BUT if `os.ReadFile()` fails for any reason (permissions, file not found, etc.), it silently continues to check other config keys instead of reporting the error\n\n**Specific problematic code block (lines 1177-1183):**\n```go\nif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))\n    if err == nil {\n        w.Write(data)\n        return\n    }\n    // BUG: If err != nil, falls through instead of handling the error\n}\n```\n\nWhen the file read fails, the code continues to check `step.Config[\"command\"]` and `step.Config[\"script\"]`, which likely don't exist, so it returns a 404 \"no content available\" error.\n\n## UI/Frontend Components\n\nThe frontend code that triggers this is in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:\n\n1. **Line 233:** Click handler that opens the step drawer\n   ```javascript\n   html += '<g class=\"dag-node\" onclick=\"openDrawer(\\'' + wf.name + '\\',\\'' + name + '\\')\" ...\n   ```\n\n2. **Lines 251-284:** The `openDrawer()` function displays step metadata and fetches content\n   ```javascript\n   function openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n       // ... displays step config (including prompt filename)\n       fetch('/api/projects/' + ... + '/content')\n           .then(function(text) {\n               if (text) {\n                   el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text + '</pre>';\n               } else {\n                   el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n               }\n           });\n   }\n   ```\n\nThe drawer shows the filename (line 264: `'<dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k]`) but fails to load the actual file contents because of the handler bug.\n\n## Files Involved\n\n- **Handler (Backend):** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199)\n- **API Endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- **Template (Frontend):** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 251-284)\n- **Styles:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (drawer styling at lines 491-549)\n\n## Next Steps\n\nTo fix this issue, the `handleAPIStepContent` function should:\n1. When `os.ReadFile()` fails for a prompt file, return an appropriate error response instead of silently falling through\n2. Or, ensure error handling is explicit for each config type check\n3. Optionally log the actual file read error to help debugging"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac4964101b4da0a5c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46748\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 19233</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a866613b-1059-4079-b5e6-a9e69f6fbbda","uuid":"8447610f-0445-49cd-a9ab-a3589df286fe","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the code related to the \"project page workflow view\" where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load file contents. This is likely a web UI component. Search thoroughly for:\n\n1. Any web UI / frontend code (HTML, JS, templates, etc.) related to workflow visualization or step display\n2. Any handler or API endpoint that serves workflow/step details\n3. Any code that deals with loading prompt file or script file contents for display\n\nSearch patterns:\n- Look for template files (*.html, *.tmpl, *.gohtml)\n- Look for handler code that serves project/workflow pages\n- Look for JavaScript that handles step click events\n- Look for any \"step\" or \"workflow\" related UI code\n- Check for terms like \"prompt\", \"script\", \"contents\", \"file\" in UI-related code\n\nBe very thorough - check cmd/, internal/, web/, static/, templates/, ui/, frontend/, and any other directories.","agentId":"ac4964101b4da0a5c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me provide a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully identified the \"project page workflow view\" issue where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load file contents. The problem is in the **API handler** that serves step content.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe bug is in the **`handleAPIStepContent` function** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199).\n\n**The Issue:** When a prompt file cannot be read (line 1177-1182), the handler falls through to the next condition instead of returning an error. This happens when:\n1. A step has a `prompt` config pointing to a file (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/fix.md`)\n2. The file exists and the path is correct\n3. BUT if `os.ReadFile()` fails for any reason (permissions, file not found, etc.), it silently continues to check other config keys instead of reporting the error\n\n**Specific problematic code block (lines 1177-1183):**\n```go\nif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))\n    if err == nil {\n        w.Write(data)\n        return\n    }\n    // BUG: If err != nil, falls through instead of handling the error\n}\n```\n\nWhen the file read fails, the code continues to check `step.Config[\"command\"]` and `step.Config[\"script\"]`, which likely don't exist, so it returns a 404 \"no content available\" error.\n\n## UI/Frontend Components\n\nThe frontend code that triggers this is in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:\n\n1. **Line 233:** Click handler that opens the step drawer\n   ```javascript\n   html += '<g class=\"dag-node\" onclick=\"openDrawer(\\'' + wf.name + '\\',\\'' + name + '\\')\" ...\n   ```\n\n2. **Lines 251-284:** The `openDrawer()` function displays step metadata and fetches content\n   ```javascript\n   function openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n       // ... displays step config (including prompt filename)\n       fetch('/api/projects/' + ... + '/content')\n           .then(function(text) {\n               if (text) {\n                   el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text + '</pre>';\n               } else {\n                   el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n               }\n           });\n   }\n   ```\n\nThe drawer shows the filename (line 264: `'<dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k]`) but fails to load the actual file contents because of the handler bug.\n\n## Files Involved\n\n- **Handler (Backend):** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199)\n- **API Endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- **Template (Frontend):** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 251-284)\n- **Styles:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (drawer styling at lines 491-549)\n\n## Next Steps\n\nTo fix this issue, the `handleAPIStepContent` function should:\n1. When `os.ReadFile()` fails for a prompt file, return an appropriate error response instead of silently falling through\n2. Or, ensure error handling is explicit for each config type check\n3. Optionally log the actual file read error to help debugging"}],"totalDurationMs":19233,"totalTokens"