{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":138705,"duration_api_ms":96183,"num_turns":21,"result":"All tests pass.\n\n**The fix:** The DSL parser stores prompt values as `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` — a raw `file(...)` wrapper string. The `handleAPIStepContent` handler was treating this raw string as a direct file path, so `os.ReadFile` would try to open a path like `/project/file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`, which doesn't exist. It silently fell through to return \"no content available\".\n\nI added a `resolveStepContent` helper (matching the existing `resolveContent` in the prompt adapter) that strips the `file(\"...\")` wrapper to extract the actual path before reading. This is applied to both `prompt` and `script` config values.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a866613b-1059-4079-b5e6-a9e69f6fbbda","total_cost_usd":0.47369745,"usage":{"input_tokens":21,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14430,"cache_read_input_tokens":424995,"output_tokens":3804,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14430,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":21,"outputTokens":3804,"cacheReadInputTokens":424995,"cacheCreationInputTokens":14430,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.39789,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":6833,"outputTokens":1695,"cacheReadInputTokens":180732,"cacheCreationInputTokens":33941,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.07580744999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"62ec6db1-7b7e-4196-ae3c-8d7e92e453e7"}
